    "# Research Questions\n",
    "\n",
    "## RQ1\n",
    "Which machine learning model provides the best predictive performance for flood probability estimation?\n",
    "\n",
    "## RQ2\n",
    "Which environmental factors contribute most significantly to flood probability prediction?\n",
    "\n",
    "## RQ3\n",
    "How can explainable AI improve transparency in climate-risk prediction systems?\n",
    "\n",
    "## RQ4\n",
    "What are the ethical implications of AI-driven flood prediction systems?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "134f6557-bda9-4667-8770-6cf1c55be445",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Results and Discussion\n",
    "\n",
    "Linear Regression achieved the strongest predictive performance with an R² score of approximately 0.845, outperforming Random Forest and XGBoost models.\n",
    "\n",
    "The results suggest that the relationships between environmental indicators and flood probability are predominantly linear in nature.\n",
    "\n",
    "Feature importance analysis and SHAP explainability identified monsoon intensity, urbanization, drainage systems, and climate-related indicators as major contributors to flood probability prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "The findings demonstrate that simpler interpretable models may outperform more complex ensemble methods when the environmental relationships within the dataset exhibit strong linear characteristics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "085e6e6d-f9cb-4df8-8d5f-a89817dca065",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Responsible AI Considerations\n",
    "\n",
    "AI-driven climate-risk prediction systems introduce important ethical and societal considerations.\n",
    "\n",
    "False negative predictions may result in inadequate disaster preparedness and delayed emergency response. False positive predictions may trigger unnecessary evacuations and economic disruption.\n",
    "\n",
    "Bias within environmental datasets may reduce model reliability across underrepresented geographic regions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Explainable AI techniques such as SHAP improve transparency and increase trustworthiness in environmental decision-support systems."
   ]
